Q1. Treatment of LE after email from Luis:

The treatment of low energy is an important feature! Since the analysis cuts at 800 MeV, I only fitted the functions 
in the range 500 MeV to 20 GeV, so the fit is valid below 800 MeV but not all the way down to 0. This was a simplifying 
choice since the cross section changes more rapidly at those low energies, but we were not selecting those events. 
Of course, you want to make sure you model the cross-section below the cut so that lateral errors are correct. So the 
radiative correction code is not valid for lower energies than that, but could be expanded if needed, following the same 
procedure.

There is no maximum energy cut on the electron sample. The way it was coded was: if the energy was higher than 19 GeV, 
that even goes into the last bin (the 9-infinity).
